Enum KBPRelationExtractor.RelationType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<KBPRelationExtractor.RelationType>
      • edu.stanford.nlp.ie.KBPRelationExtractor.RelationType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<KBPRelationExtractor.RelationType>
    Enclosing interface:
    KBPRelationExtractor

    public static enum KBPRelationExtractor.RelationType
extends Enum<KBPRelationExtractor.RelationType>
    Known relation types (last updated for the 2013 shared task). Note that changing the constants here can have far-reaching consequences in loading serialized models, and various bits of code that have been hard-coded to these relation types (e.g., the various consistency filters).

    Note: Neither per:spouse, org:founded_by, or X:organizations_founded are SINGLE relations in the spec - these are made single here because our system otherwise over-predicts them.

    Author:
    Gabor Angeli

    • Field Detail

      • canonicalName

        public final String canonicalName
        A canonical name for this relation type. This is the official 2010 relation name, that has since changed.

      • isOriginalRelation

        public final boolean isOriginalRelation
        If true, realtation was one of the original (non-inverse) KBP relation.

      • queryLimit

        public final int queryLimit
        A guess of the maximum number of results to query for this relation. Only really relevant for cold start.

      • entityType

        public final KBPRelationExtractor.NERTag entityType
        The entity type (left arg type) associated with this relation. That is, either a PERSON or an ORGANIZATION "slot".

      • cardinality

        public final KBPRelationExtractor.RelationType.Cardinality cardinality
        The cardinality of this entity. That is, can multiple right arguments participate in this relation (born_in vs. lived_in)

      • validNamedEntityLabels

        public final Set<KBPRelationExtractor.NERTag> validNamedEntityLabels
        Valid named entity labels for the right argument to this relation

      • validPOSPrefixes

        public final Set<String> validPOSPrefixes
        Valid POS [prefixes] for the right argument to this relation (e.g., can only take nouns, or can only take numbers, etc.)

      • priorProbability

        public final double priorProbability
        The prior for how often this relation occurs in the training data. Note that this prior is not necessarily accurate for the test data.

      • plausiblyHasRelation

        public static boolean plausiblyHasRelation(KBPRelationExtractor.NERTag entityType,
                                           KBPRelationExtractor.NERTag slotValueType)
        Returns whether two entity types could plausibly have a relation hold between them. That is, is there a known relation type that would hold between these two entity types.
        Parameters:
        entityType - The NER tag of the entity.
        slotValueType - The NER tag of the slot value.
        Returns:
        True if there is a plausible relation which could occur between these two types.
